A function $ f$ is defined by $ f(z) = i\bar z$, where $ i =\sqrt{-\!1}$ and $ \bar z$ is the complex conjugate of $ z$. How many values of $ z$ satisfy both $ |z| = 5$ and $ f (z) = z$?\\
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ 0 \qquad
\textbf{(B)}\ 1 \qquad
\textbf{(C)}\ 2 \qquad
\textbf{(D)}\ 4 \qquad
\textbf{(E)}\ 8$
